Address: 3133 Ann Arbor-Saline Rd, Ann Arbor, MI 48103
Description: Lively chain steakhouse serving American fare with a Southwestern spin amid Texas-themed decor.

summary.snippet: "Great service great food decent prices cool vibe great for family or for a date."
"I ordered a NY strip steak, side of ribs, loaded potato, and green beans."
"We were quickly seated with rolls, butter and peanuts on the table."

most_relevant.description: After a long time on the try list, I finally had dinner on Friday with a colleague at this delightful restaurant. The complimentary bread was amazing and set the tone for a great meal. I ordered the grilled BBQ chicken with veggies and rice, and the rice was particularly memorable, reminiscent of flavorful biryani. The host was both cute and beautiful, adding a pleasant touch to the evening. The service was attentive and friendly, enhancing the overall experience. Additionally, the restaurant offers free ample parking, which is a definite plus. Overall, a satisfying dining experience that exceeded expectations.
Food was good, but deadass spent two hours inside this restaurant waiting for our food, which came one by one. Genuinely think I aged three years waiting here.

Party of 8 seated immediately when arrived.  Had a great waiter>Mel who was on top of things. He had our order right & kept our drinks filled. Food was cooked right, tasted delicious, and served fast.  Celebrated a birthday & they did a special thing for him
Was a good experience.  A bit on the pricey side >  $245.95 for 6 adults & 2 kids. But we already know the price before going. Had a good dinner & a great time.

Today we had a very bad experience in this place, 1st.-the food took over 30 mins to come to the table, we were not longer hungry after the food came, 2nd- we ordered the Ribeye 12 oz medium/well plus ribs (combo) [2 orders the same] with baked potato and cesar salad. After waiting for over 30 minutes the ribeyes came well done and dry, the potatos were super salty and also dry and one of the ribs came almost like a charcoal, super burned and black, we returned that rib no even a dog could eat it, and they brought another piece  of rib almost 15 mins lataer or when we were finishing eating the over cooked and dry beef, we order a Blue Moon and the second one the glass was broken on the border, I returned it and they offered me another one and I said no, enough, I was already fed off and ready to leave the place for the bad service and low food quality, it was a very bad experience, several issues in the food quality and service, I will not recommend this place to my friends and with me they lost one customer. I would not recomend this place.

We enjoyed a great dinner. Our servers, Gracie, and Maddison did an excellent job.  Our dinners were very good and cooked just the way we asked them to be. The restaurant was very busy and very loud, before the amount of people in there it was very clean, and the restrooms were very clean.

Only redeeming quality for this place was the service. Food was COVERED in visible coarse flaky salt. I ordered ribs and a baked potato. Literally couldn’t eat it.
Server sent the manager over - her resolution was to let the kitchen staff know to use less salt for the next customer.
If you’re looking for a salt lick for dinner…. You’ve found your spot

The food was Delicious
The employees are ALL Awesome

Had a great experience at this location! Came here for my mom's birthday dinner. We had a large party so we had two booths, our server was amazing. She made sure we had bread rolls at all times and full drinks. Food was great as always! Wait was short!
